# Copy to `.env` for local LAN testing (file is gitignored).
#
# Metro / dev client cannot connect (e.g. error to 192.0.0.2:8081):
# 1) Prefer: npm run start:dev:tunnel  (works across Wi‑Fi / USB / VPN)
# 2) Or same Wi‑Fi: npm run start:dev:lan  and set your Mac LAN IP:
#    export REACT_NATIVE_PACKAGER_HOSTNAME=192.168.x.x && npm run start:dev
# 3) USB + adb: adb reverse tcp:8081 tcp:8081  then in dev client use host localhost port 8081
#
# EAS Internal builds: set BRIDGE_INTERNAL_SECRET in Expo → Project → Environment variables / Secrets
# so it is available at build time (same name: BRIDGE_INTERNAL_SECRET).

# Required for Bridge API auth when using bridgeClient
BRIDGE_INTERNAL_SECRET=

# Optional — only to override Render defaults (see app.config.js)
# APP_API_URL_OVERRIDE=http://192.168.x.x:3004
# APP_BRIDGE_API_URL=http://192.168.x.x:3012
# APP_ENGLIVO_API_URL=http://192.168.x.x:3000

# Optional — override Clerk publishable key (defaults in app.config.js)
# EXPO_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_...
